## PROMPT — YEAR 2: Extensibility & Ecosystem

**Context.**
Year 1 closed at 50k MAU with a working plugin API v0. The roadmap-voting page shows what people want. There's a tail of feature requests we can't all build ourselves.

**Mission.**
Become a platform: third parties can build on Zoc AI, ship plugins, integrate models, add languages. Hit 250k MAU on the back of the ecosystem.

**Strategic priorities.**
1. **Plugin SDK v1** in TypeScript + Python + Rust. Sandboxed execution (WASM for untrusted code). Capabilities-based permissions.
2. **Plugin marketplace**: discovery UI inside the app, signed packages, ratings, search. Hosted as a static index on Cloudflare R2 with a community-moderated submission process.
3. **Custom agent recipes**: declarative YAML/JSON agents users compose without code (think GitHub Actions for the agent loop). Recipes are first-class plugins.
4. **Model marketplace integration**: one-click download from HuggingFace, llama.cpp registry. Quantization picker. Per-model benchmarks shown in the picker.
5. **Language packs as plugins**: tree-sitter grammars + LSP adapters bundled as plugins. Ship 20 official packs (TS, Python, Rust, Go, Java, C, C++, C#, Ruby, PHP, Swift, Kotlin, Zig, Elixir, Lua, Haskell, OCaml, Scala, Clojure, SQL).
6. **Multi-modal input**: screenshot → code (Vision model integration), voice → chat (local Whisper.cpp), document upload (PDF / Markdown → embedded context).
7. **Public benchmark suite** (alpha): "Zoc AI Bench" — a public set of tasks we run all supported models against, results published quarterly.

**Non-negotiables.**
- Plugins cannot bypass tool-permission prompts. The capability system is non-negotiable.
- Marketplace listings can be removed (and signing keys revoked) for malicious plugins.
- No paid-only marketplace tier in Year 2 — keep the ecosystem free and frictionless first.

**Year-end exit criteria.**
- 200+ third-party plugins.
- 250k MAU.
- 5+ enterprise design partners on a private build (seed for Year 3).
- Multi-modal pipeline works on at least 3 local model families.

**Out of scope.**
- Teams SaaS (Year 3).
- Real-time pair editing.
- Background long-running agents (Year 4).

**Hand-off to Year 3.**
Decide: which 3 enterprise design partners do we turn into the first paying Teams customers?

