## PROMPT — YEAR 4: Agentic Autonomy

**Context.**
Year 3 closed at $5M ARR with Teams + Enterprise. Knowledge graph is shipping value. Users now want longer-running, less hand-held agentic tasks.

**Mission.**
Move from "agent on your turn" to "agent on a long task." Background workflows that produce reviewable PRs over hours or days, self-improving prompts, multi-agent orchestration. Hit 3M MAU.

**Strategic priorities.**
1. **Durable background workflows**:
   - Embed a Temporal-lite workflow engine in the sidecar.
   - Hand the agent a multi-day project ("migrate this service from Express to Hono"); it works in the background, surfaces progress + draft PRs.
   - Pause / resume / cancel / inspect from the UI.
   - Resilient to restarts (workflow state persisted).
2. **Self-improving prompts**:
   - Per-workspace prompt-learning store (private, on-device).
   - Agent learns from accept/reject signal which tool-selection heuristics and prompt phrasings work best in this codebase.
   - Surface a "Reset learning" button — never silent.
3. **Reasoning model integration**:
   - First-class support for thinking models (o-series equivalents and any local reasoning model).
   - Collapsible reasoning traces in the UI; copy/share reasoning + answer separately.
4. **Specialized fine-tunes** (curated bundle):
   - Ship a small library of fine-tuned models: SQL, React, Rust, Go, Python data science, Terraform.
   - Opt-in, downloaded on demand, under a permissive license.
   - Routing layer: agent auto-picks the right specialist based on the task and context.
5. **Multi-agent orchestration**:
   - "Manager" agent decomposes tasks and delegates to specialist agents in parallel.
   - Single review surface: the user sees all proposed changes from all sub-agents in one diff stack.
   - Visualize the agent graph live in the UI.
6. **"Zoc AI Bench" public leaderboard**:
   - Open-source benchmark with category leaderboards (refactor, bug-fix, test-gen, doc-gen, migration).
   - Monthly published results across all major local + hosted models.

**Non-negotiables.**
- A background task can only run inside an approved workspace. Permissions same as interactive tasks.
- Reasoning traces never leak to telemetry.
- The user can always inspect, pause, cancel.

**Year-end exit criteria.**
- 30% of accepted diffs originate from background tasks (vs interactive prompts).
- Long-running task success rate (compiles + tests pass) > 75% on the public bench.
- 3M MAU.
- Reasoning model integration shipping for at least 3 model families.

**Out of scope.**
- Mobile (Year 5).
- Hardware-vendor partnerships (Year 5).

**Hand-off to Year 5.**
Pick: foundation governance model. Apache vs Linux Foundation vs new dedicated foundation.

